Description: Rest on the flight into Egypt, after Christoph Schwarz; a landscape with the Holy family resting in the left foreground, the Virgin sitting underneath a palm tree and suckling Christ, St Joseph sitting with his head resting on his hand at far left, a hat and three pears before him; two angels appear above them; the ass grazes nearby; in the distance, at right, a fortified city Engraving
Producer name: Print made by: Jan Sadeler I
Bibliographic references: Hollstein / Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts c.1450-1700 (302)
Acquisition notes: For comment on the probable provenance from Sir Hans Sloane, see D,7.1 with no indication of provenance on verso
